articles.description: Freshman Zach Cooks hit two free throws with four seconds left to give NJIT a 71-69 win over Jacksonville in an Atlantic Sun Conference battle Thursday night.
articles.headline: Zach Cooks free throws lift NJIT past Jacksonville, 71-68

articles.description: Jordan Giles and Brandon McKissic each had 17 points and Isaiah Ross added 14 as UMKC beat Chicago State 76-67 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Giles and McKissic combine for 34 as UMKC outlasts Cougars

articles.description: Grant Riller drilled a game-winning 3-pointer with 2.2 seconds left in overtime to lift College of Charleston to an 81-78 Colonial Athletic Association victory Thursday night.
articles.headline: Charleston keeps CAA lead, beats James Madison in OT, 81-78

articles.description: Scottie James scored 23 points and grabbed 15 rebounds and Liberty blanked UNC Asheville in overtime in an 82-69 victory Thursday night that snapped the Bulldogs' 21-game home win streak.
articles.headline: Liberty wins in OT, ends Asheville's 21-game home win streak

articles.description: Senior Xavier Cooks poured in a career-high 36 points and added season highs of 16 rebounds and six blocked shots to power Winthrop to a 90-71 victory over Gardner-Webb on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Cooks' effort leads Winthrop past Gardner-Webb 90-71

articles.description: Jordon Varnado hit a jumper and Kevin Barker split a pair of free throws to complete a late Troy rally to slip past Coastal Carolina 66-65 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Troy rallies late to beat Coastal Carolina 66-65

videos.description: Valparaiso's Joe Burton breaks out the Eurostep and finishes the layup.
videos.headline: Burton nails Eurostep layup

videos.description: After the block from Purdue's Isaac Haas, Vincent Edwards feeds Carsen Edwards down low for the and-1 layup.
videos.headline: Edwards-to-Edwards connection leads to and-1

videos.description: Valparaiso's Derrik Smits gets the ball in the post and goes right by Matt Haarms for the layup.
videos.headline: Smits breezes by Haarms

videos.description: Purdue's Nojel Eastern finds Ryan Cline open behind the arc for the deep 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Cline knocks down long 3-pointer

videos.description: Following the steal from Purdue's Vincent Edwards on the defensive end, Dakota Mathias finds Carsen Edwards cutting down the lane for the contested layup.
videos.headline: Mathias finds Edwards for tough layup

videos.description: Purdue's Isaac Haas gets the ball in the post and backs down Derrik Smits for the contested finish.
videos.headline: Haas finishes tough shot in post

videos.description: After getting double teamed in the post, Purdue's Isaac Haas swings the ball to Vincent Edwards down for the easy layup in the first half.
videos.headline: Haas' great pass sets up easy finish

videos.description: Purdue's Vincent Edwards drives down the paint and kicks the ball out to Dakota Mathias for the contested 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Edwards finds Mathias for the 3

videos.description: With the shot clock running low, Purdue's Dakota Mathias finds P.J. Thompson in the corner for the 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Thompson beats the buzzer with 3-pointer

videos.description: Valparaiso's Bakari Evelyn finds Max Joseph cutting down the lane for a chance at a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Joseph's acrobatic layup earns chance at 3-point play

videos.description: After getting the rebound on the defensive end, Purdue's Carsen Edwards goes coast-to-coast and finishes the tough layup.
videos.headline: Edwards splits the Crusaders' defense for 3-point chance

videos.description: After faking out two defenders with the shot fake, Purdue's Vincent Edwards spins around and knocks down the hook shot.
videos.headline: Edwards' pump fake sets up hook shot

videos.description: Despite the contact from Valparaiso's Markus Golder, Purdue's Nojel Eastern sinks the mid-range jumper for a chance at a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Eastern knocks down tough jumper for 3-point chance
